title: Vikings' Rowan wins pair of WHSFL awards
text:
Vikings' Rowan wins pair of WHSFL awards By: Uncredited Report Error 
Tyler Rowan took home a pair of honours on Wednesday as he was named the Winnipeg High School Football League’s Kas Vidruk (AA) Division offensive and special teams player of the week. 
The Vincent Massey Vikings running back rushed 19 times for 191 yards and a pair of touchdowns as they handed the visiting River East Kodiaks their first loss of the season in a 
23-16 decision. Rowan earned the special teams award after averaging 37 yards on his eight punts and pinning the Kodiaks inside their 10-yard line three times — two of which were inside the five. 
The Vikings (2-4) close out the regular season on Friday when they visit the Steinbach Sabres (5-1). Meanwhile the Crocus Plainsmen (1-5) host the Kildonan East Reivers (0-6) today at 3 p.m 
The Neelin Spartans (2-3) will be in Dryden on Friday to visit the Eagles (5-1) in their Andy Currie (A) Division season finale.
